[SN]TITLE[SN]
Lee Clark: Kilmarnock to appoint former Blackpool manager

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Lee Clark is to become the new manager of Scottish Premiership strugglers Kilmarnock.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The former Huddersfield, Birmingham City and Blackpool boss is expected to be announced as Gary Locke's replacement on Monday morning.
Locke, 40, resigned last month following the 1-0 home defeat by Hamilton Academical.
Ex-Newcastle, Sunderland and Fulham player Clark, 43, has not managed since leaving Blackpool last year.
His resignation followed the Seasiders' relegation to League One.
