Killie moved out of the Scottish Premiership's bottom two with victory over Motherwell on Saturday.
Player-coach Lee McCulloch, who has been in interim charge of the Rugby Park side for their last two matches, will remain as assistant manager to Clark.
The Ayrshire side host Rangers in Tuesday's Scottish Cup fifth-round replay.
